      "honoree": {
        "name": "Corrections Officer Joseph Gomm",
        "summary": "Corrections Officer Joseph Gomm was beaten to death by an inmate at Minnesota Correction Facility–Stillwater at approximately 1:30 p.m. He was supervising inmates in the prison's industry building when he was attacked by one inmate with a hammer. Officer Gomm was transported to Regions Hospital, in St. Paul, where he succumbed to his injuries. Officer Gomm had served with the Minnesota Department of Corrections for 16 years. He is survived by his mother, three brothers and two sisters. In August 2019, a portion of MN state highway 95, running from Interstate 94 in Lakeland to MN state Highway 36 in Oak Park Heights, was renamed Corrections Officer Joseph Gomm Memorial Highway.",
